WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:02.703
- Previously on Nashville...

00:02.736 --> 00:04.705
- * Sweet revenge

00:04.738 --> 00:06.540
- You're amazing.
- Oh, thanks.

00:06.574 --> 00:09.177
- My name's Avery, and--
- We're looking for someone.

00:09.210 --> 00:10.178
- Somebody exactly like you.

00:10.211 --> 00:11.379
- Okay.

00:11.412 --> 00:13.681
- I guess I don't know much
about equine therapy at all.

00:13.714 --> 00:15.749
- It's transformational.

00:15.783 --> 00:18.519
Sean, you want to
give it a try?

00:18.552 --> 00:20.154
- No, that's okay.

00:20.188 --> 00:22.256
My nephew. He's staying
with us for a while.

00:25.726 --> 00:27.261
- I'm sorry.

00:27.295 --> 00:28.629
- Deacon, it's okay.

00:34.368 --> 00:36.370
- Maddie, can you
come here for a sec?

00:37.838 --> 00:39.440
- Can you please,
please come to this

00:39.473 --> 00:41.142
stupid Art Walk thing
with us, please?

00:41.175 --> 00:42.810
- I can't. I'm going
to hang out with Jonah.

00:42.843 --> 00:44.512
- Jonah, Jonah, Jonah.
Please?

00:44.545 --> 00:45.646
- I thought you
loved that thing?

00:45.679 --> 00:47.348
- Yeah, when I was 10.

00:47.381 --> 00:48.816
And definitely not
with Jake Maitland.

00:48.849 --> 00:50.484
- I thought you guys were good.

00:50.518 --> 00:52.186
- That does not mean
I wanna go hang out with him

00:52.220 --> 00:53.721
while Dad and Jessie are...

00:53.754 --> 00:55.789
- Oh, that's what
this is about.

00:55.823 --> 00:57.525
- No. It's definitely not
what this is about!

00:57.558 --> 00:58.859
This is about me being
dragged around

00:58.892 --> 01:00.561
like some little girl
that does not know

01:00.594 --> 01:01.662
how to take care of herself!

01:01.695 --> 01:03.131
- Okay.

01:03.164 --> 01:05.499
You're gonna survive,
I promise.

01:05.533 --> 01:07.067
I have to go get ready.

01:13.474 --> 01:14.842
- Dude, this is crazy.

01:14.875 --> 01:16.810
All anybody's talking
about is Alannah.

01:16.844 --> 01:18.279
- Awesome.

01:18.312 --> 01:20.581
- It's like
we weren't even there.

01:20.614 --> 01:21.582
What are you looking for?

01:21.615 --> 01:25.319
- My... vitamins.

01:25.353 --> 01:27.321
They were in my gym bag
and now they're not.

01:27.355 --> 01:28.822
Are you like 80?

01:28.856 --> 01:30.324
- Sorry I'm late, guys.

01:30.358 --> 01:33.727
- Hey, any, uh...
any word from Juliette?

01:33.761 --> 01:37.765
- No, and Cadence cried from
three a.m. to sunrise.

01:37.798 --> 01:39.533
- I'm sorry, man.

01:39.567 --> 01:43.204
- Yeah, it'll be fine.
It's only for two weeks.

01:43.237 --> 01:44.905
I'm just so mad that
she would leave that way.

01:44.938 --> 01:48.576
Anyway, you guys read
the reactions to the show?

01:48.609 --> 01:51.379
- Oh, yeah.
- Yep.

01:51.412 --> 01:53.647
- You know, at least people
are talking about us.

01:53.681 --> 01:55.283
Maybe she's just
what was missing.

01:55.316 --> 01:58.186
- I don't know.

01:58.219 --> 01:59.620
We just figured out our sound.

01:59.653 --> 02:01.522
Now she changes everything.

02:01.555 --> 02:02.756
- I hate to break it to you,

02:02.790 --> 02:04.292
but the genie's
out of the bottle.

02:06.427 --> 02:08.629
- Well, great.
What do we call ourselves?

02:08.662 --> 02:09.897
Three Men and a Lady?

02:11.665 --> 02:13.267
I'm seriously getting
worried about you.

02:15.636 --> 02:17.171
Listen, I get it.

02:17.205 --> 02:18.806
I mean, it's not
how we imagined this.

02:18.839 --> 02:20.741
But we'd be stupid
not to try it.

02:22.743 --> 02:24.378
Will, don't just leave.

02:24.412 --> 02:25.613
Come on, let's talk about it.
- Will, dude.

02:25.646 --> 02:26.914
- Oh, what is there
to talk about?

02:26.947 --> 02:28.516
Y'all made up
your minds already.

02:35.523 --> 02:37.391
- So now we're gonna
attach our family appliques

02:37.425 --> 02:39.260
to our quilt tops.

02:39.293 --> 02:41.562
- This looks just beautiful.

02:41.595 --> 02:42.863
Do you mind if I join you?

02:42.896 --> 02:44.632
- Not at all.
- Thanks.

02:44.665 --> 02:46.434
What y'all got going on here?

02:46.467 --> 02:49.803
- Anyone wanna tell Scarlett
about their riding blankets?

02:49.837 --> 02:52.306
Kaitlyn
How about you?

02:54.575 --> 02:55.909
All right.

02:55.943 --> 02:57.478
Well, make sure you get
both layers of fabric

02:57.511 --> 02:58.946
with each stitch.

02:58.979 --> 03:01.915
And make sure your stitches
are evenly spaced.

03:04.652 --> 03:06.254
- I know who you are.

03:07.588 --> 03:09.790
- You're from the band,
The Exes?

03:09.823 --> 03:12.326
- I was.

03:12.360 --> 03:14.462
- Will you sing
for us sometime?

03:16.630 --> 03:19.567
If y'all finish
your projects there,

03:19.600 --> 03:21.969
I reckon we can work
something out. Deal?

03:39.687 --> 03:41.322
- Hey, thanks for coming.

03:41.355 --> 03:42.990
- I can't believe it.

03:43.023 --> 03:44.992
- My mother used to play
"Beneath Still Waters"

03:45.025 --> 03:47.695
over and over.
It kills me every time.

03:47.728 --> 03:49.397
- Very cool.
- Thanks.

03:49.430 --> 03:50.864
- You know, speaking of
killing it,

03:50.898 --> 03:52.833
the reason I wanted to meet
is our Twitter feed

03:52.866 --> 03:53.834
exploded after the show
last night.

03:53.867 --> 03:55.503
- Yeah.

03:55.536 --> 03:57.438
- That's great.
I'm not really into Twitter.

03:57.471 --> 03:59.507
- Oh, well, you're lucky,
but, yeah.

03:59.540 --> 04:00.741
It's great.

04:00.774 --> 04:02.343
- Well, congrats.
That's awesome.

04:02.376 --> 04:04.044
I thought you guys
were amazing.

04:04.077 --> 04:06.780
- Not for us.
For you.

04:09.049 --> 04:11.485
That's cool, I guess.

04:11.519 --> 04:12.886
- Yeah.

04:12.920 --> 04:15.623
Well, I was talking to
the boys this morning

04:15.656 --> 04:17.858
and we all really love what
you bring in the group.

04:17.891 --> 04:22.363
Even debating whether we should
make you a bigger part.

04:22.396 --> 04:24.031
- Well, look, I'm flattered.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.933
But, you know,
you three have a thing.

04:25.966 --> 04:27.601
And I'm...

04:27.635 --> 04:30.037
- Hey, look, we all want this.
What do you think?

04:32.406 --> 04:35.909
- I think you three drank
too much whiskey last night.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.511
- Maybe not enough.

04:38.846 --> 04:40.481
Come on.
What are you afraid of?

04:40.514 --> 04:43.317
- I came to Nashville
to be a singer-songwriter.

04:43.351 --> 04:44.585
I don't wanna lose that.

04:47.421 --> 04:48.922
- You don't even
know my music.

04:48.956 --> 04:52.025
- Well, I know last night
was special.

04:52.059 --> 04:53.961
Come on.
What do you lose by trying?

04:53.994 --> 04:56.464
- I'll tell you what.

04:56.497 --> 04:58.432
Why don't you come
by my place tomorrow night?

04:58.466 --> 05:02.736
I'll play you a few of my songs,
and you'll see what you think.

05:02.770 --> 05:03.704
How's that sound?

05:08.576 --> 05:11.545
- Ah, yes.
Tiny headed horse.

05:11.579 --> 05:12.880
- And a dog.
- Look at that over there.

05:12.913 --> 05:14.815
That's kind of cool.
- I like that.

05:14.848 --> 05:16.784
- Oh, that's awesome.
- I've worked with that guy.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.118
Was it fun?

05:18.151 --> 05:20.621
- That was a good time.

05:22.823 --> 05:24.458
- I like that one.

05:24.492 --> 05:26.059
- Do you think that's
a Landry Major photo?

05:26.093 --> 05:27.695
- I don't know,
but it's great.

05:27.728 --> 05:29.663
- Can you imagine being in
the water like that

05:29.697 --> 05:32.065
at a full gallop with
a lasso in your hand?

05:32.099 --> 05:34.101
- I can't even walk and
chew gum at the same time.

05:34.134 --> 05:36.837
- You can just
feel the movement.

05:36.870 --> 05:39.840
You know, when I was a kid,
I was just obsessed

05:39.873 --> 05:41.542
with shooting for
the National Geographic.

05:41.575 --> 05:43.711
- Yeah.

05:45.446 --> 05:50.418
- Um, I don't know.
I guess...

05:50.451 --> 05:52.386
I guess life had other plans.

05:52.420 --> 05:54.021
- Wish my life had other plans.

05:55.756 --> 05:57.525
- Oh, I'm sorry.
I got carried away.

05:57.558 --> 05:58.759
Isn't this amazing?

06:00.027 --> 06:01.595
- Yeah, I guess so.

06:03.897 --> 06:05.165
Can we go?

06:05.198 --> 06:06.667
- Yeah, we can get outta here.

06:06.700 --> 06:08.702
- No. Actually,
I'd like to see more.

06:11.872 --> 06:13.073
- All right.

06:13.106 --> 06:14.642
Oh, man. Come on, guys.

06:14.675 --> 06:15.709
- It's all right, it's okay.
- Okay.

06:15.743 --> 06:16.977
- Sure.

06:31.692 --> 06:32.760
- Sweetie, it's me.
Can I come in?

06:36.564 --> 06:38.899
- I'm just about
to hop in the shower.

06:41.134 --> 06:43.070
- Okay. Well, maybe we can find
a minute tomorrow.

06:43.103 --> 06:44.137
We can talk?

06:47.675 --> 06:49.009
- Okay.

06:49.042 --> 06:50.210
- 'Night.

06:50.243 --> 06:51.745
- Goodnight.

07:14.735 --> 07:16.770
- There's our miracle worker.

07:18.271 --> 07:19.640
- It means you finally
motivated those two girls

07:19.673 --> 07:21.475
to actually do something.

07:21.509 --> 07:22.743
- Oh...
- It was very generous of you.

07:22.776 --> 07:23.744
Thank you.

07:25.078 --> 07:26.580
- I keep trying to
break free of that life.

07:26.614 --> 07:28.716
But it just keeps on
reigning me back in.

07:28.749 --> 07:30.684
- Things don't really go away
till they taught us

07:30.718 --> 07:32.085
what we need to learn.

07:32.119 --> 07:34.021
- Guess I'm a slow learner.

07:34.054 --> 07:36.624
- I doubt that.
You have a gift.

07:36.657 --> 07:38.659
How you choose to
use it is up to you.

07:40.561 --> 07:41.795
- Thanks.

07:44.197 --> 07:50.070
I saw him yesterday talking
to a woman in the parking lot.

07:50.103 --> 07:52.139
She was crying
and holding a child.

07:52.172 --> 07:54.775
It was one of the
saddest things I ever saw.

07:54.808 --> 07:56.877
- He was the sweetest boy
you ever met.

07:56.910 --> 07:58.178
And they broke him.

07:59.212 --> 08:00.881
- Sean was so talented.

08:00.914 --> 08:03.717
He could have given John Mayer
a run for his money.

08:05.052 --> 08:06.820
- In his case,
nothing physical.

08:06.854 --> 08:09.890
He just saw and heard things
that no one should see or hear.

08:11.625 --> 08:13.193
- His wife, Angela.

08:13.226 --> 08:15.128
High school sweethearts.

08:15.162 --> 08:16.997
I don't know how much longer
she's gonna hang in, though.

08:18.932 --> 08:21.301
So you see, Miss Scarlett,
we're all healing

08:21.334 --> 08:24.004
one way or another
together.

08:24.037 --> 08:26.907
Be patient with yourself.

08:26.940 --> 08:28.609
- Thank you.

08:35.215 --> 08:36.784
- Oh!

08:36.817 --> 08:38.652
- No.

08:38.686 --> 08:39.720
- Thanks.

08:43.190 --> 08:44.825
- Nothing.

08:44.858 --> 08:46.193
- It's not
what you're thinking.

08:46.226 --> 08:47.928
- Sure. Whatever.

08:47.961 --> 08:49.196
Is that my cologne?

08:49.229 --> 08:50.798
- Somebody's hangry.

08:50.831 --> 08:52.199
- Nobody's hangry, Romeo.

08:52.232 --> 08:54.034
Where you taking her?

08:54.067 --> 08:55.769
- I told you,
it's not like that.

08:55.803 --> 08:56.970
We're just going to her house.

08:57.004 --> 08:58.939
- Fast lane.
- No.

08:58.972 --> 09:00.941
To listen to her music
for our band, asshat.

09:00.974 --> 09:02.242
- Uh-huh.

09:02.275 --> 09:04.177
- To see if it
suits our style!

09:04.211 --> 09:05.713
- Just remember what
happened the last time

09:05.746 --> 09:07.147
you slept with a band member.

09:07.180 --> 09:09.149
- Hey, that is low.

09:09.182 --> 09:10.684
- I'm just saying
don't be an idiot.

09:10.718 --> 09:13.053
- I will not be an idiot!

09:18.826 --> 09:20.127
- Hey.
- Hey.

09:20.160 --> 09:21.829
- I'm sorry.

09:21.862 --> 09:23.030
Everything is still a little
crazy with Zach gone.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.698
- It's okay.

09:24.732 --> 09:26.834
- I'll think about.

09:29.136 --> 09:30.337
Let's do this old school.

09:30.370 --> 09:31.839
- Oh...
- Yeah.

09:31.872 --> 09:33.173
- Wow, people are
gonna start talking.

09:33.206 --> 09:35.208
- Let 'em talk.

09:37.110 --> 09:39.012
- It was all right.

09:39.046 --> 09:40.648
- Well, that's convincing.

09:44.351 --> 09:45.318
I just can't stop
thinking about last night.

09:46.720 --> 09:48.388
- The way Daphne
was treating you.

09:48.421 --> 09:50.624
- Oh... what are
you talking about?

09:50.658 --> 09:51.992
- Come on now.

09:52.025 --> 09:53.661
She hardly said
two words to you.

09:53.694 --> 09:54.928
She was rude as hell.
- Oh, please.

09:56.864 --> 09:58.165
- She wasn't raised that way.
I can tell you that much.

09:58.198 --> 09:59.867
- Well, she's a teenager.

09:59.900 --> 10:01.969
Don't you think you're
making too much of this?

10:02.002 --> 10:03.704
- Funny, didn't you say
you didn't feel anything?

10:03.737 --> 10:07.074
- I mean, I noticed
something, sure.

10:07.107 --> 10:08.742
But it's not like I was
upset about it or anything.

10:08.776 --> 10:11.144
- That's 'cause
you're too nice.

10:11.178 --> 10:13.213
I just feel like I need
to head this thing off somehow

10:13.246 --> 10:15.148
or it's just gonna get worse.

10:15.182 --> 10:16.717
- You're gonna talk
to her about it.

10:16.750 --> 10:17.951
- I might, yeah.

10:17.985 --> 10:19.787
- Oh, wow.

10:19.820 --> 10:21.288
You know, she's just gonna
end up hating me even more.

10:21.321 --> 10:23.657
- She doesn't hate you, Jessie.
- I would hate me.

10:26.193 --> 10:27.928
- Look, I don't know
what I'm gonna do.

10:27.961 --> 10:31.098
But I think I need
to do something.

10:31.131 --> 10:32.866
- Well, I think we should
just forget about it

10:32.900 --> 10:34.201
for the rest of the night.

10:36.169 --> 10:38.772
- Okay.

10:38.806 --> 10:41.875
- * You're like swimming
in the river in the darkness *

10:41.909 --> 10:44.878
* Never have to question
where my heart is *

10:44.912 --> 10:49.249
* No need to test the water,
I just jump right in *

10:51.118 --> 10:53.453
* We're washing every worry
in the water *

10:53.486 --> 10:57.725
* You and I
in the middle of somewhere *

10:57.758 --> 11:02.830
* You and the moon
gonna take me now *

11:04.297 --> 11:08.301
* Ooh hoo hoo

11:08.335 --> 11:10.804
* We are just river swimming

11:10.838 --> 11:14.975
* Ooh hoo hoo

11:17.077 --> 11:22.716
* Ooh hoo hoo

11:25.418 --> 11:27.821
- Wow.
- Yeah.

11:27.855 --> 11:30.157
I can do better,
but you got the drift.

11:30.190 --> 11:31.825
- Seriously, I mean...

11:31.859 --> 11:33.994
Where'd you learn
to spin a story like that?

11:34.027 --> 11:36.063
- I don't know.

11:36.096 --> 11:37.831
I mean, it's kind of like
asking how I learnt

11:37.865 --> 11:40.834
to walk or talk or breathe.

11:44.437 --> 11:46.306
- My mother.

11:46.339 --> 11:49.276
Yeah, she, um...
she loved country music.

11:49.309 --> 11:50.510
Loved it.

11:50.543 --> 11:53.380
- Hated it.

11:53.413 --> 11:55.248
Called it hillbilly
funeral music.

11:59.152 --> 12:02.522
Each night when
he left for work,

12:02.555 --> 12:05.458
she'd pour herself a drink,

12:05.492 --> 12:07.527
and play her favorite records.

12:07.560 --> 12:10.798
Emmylou, Loretta...

12:10.831 --> 12:12.332
- Just a...

12:12.365 --> 12:14.067
- Oop!

12:14.101 --> 12:16.169
Joan Baez.

12:16.203 --> 12:18.438
You know, she totally
had a thing

12:18.471 --> 12:21.008
for strong resilient women.

12:21.041 --> 12:23.510
That's probably why

12:23.543 --> 12:25.512
nothing changed
when he left for good.

12:27.180 --> 12:29.416
She just kept
playing her records

12:29.449 --> 12:31.084
and doing the laundry

12:31.118 --> 12:33.220
and washing the dishes

12:33.253 --> 12:35.155
and making sure
I had what I needed.

12:35.188 --> 12:36.890
- Hmm.

12:36.924 --> 12:40.293
- Turns out all those women
were just singing

12:40.327 --> 12:42.295
what she was feeling.

12:42.329 --> 12:47.134
Kind of reminding her that
she wasn't alone, you know.

12:47.167 --> 12:50.503
That heartache is just
another rite of passage.

12:52.139 --> 12:54.207
- So that's
what the song's about?

12:54.241 --> 12:56.944
Heartbreak?

12:56.977 --> 12:58.011
- No.

12:59.880 --> 13:02.449
It's about...

13:02.482 --> 13:06.119
letting go of something
before you break it.

13:06.153 --> 13:07.454
Or before it breaks you.

13:09.489 --> 13:11.892
I guess that's
what I learnt from her.

13:14.194 --> 13:15.863
- Beneath still waters.

13:23.236 --> 13:25.105
- Um, so...

13:25.138 --> 13:26.573
- So...

13:31.611 --> 13:34.081
- The band.

13:34.114 --> 13:35.983
- Yeah.

13:36.016 --> 13:38.919
Yeah, I mean,
no, the band.

13:38.952 --> 13:40.520
Rehearsal tomorrow?

13:40.553 --> 13:41.989
Rework some of the songs
for the show

13:42.022 --> 13:45.225
and play the boys
a couple of yours?

13:45.258 --> 13:46.193
- Cool.

13:47.995 --> 13:49.096
- Yeah.

13:51.664 --> 13:53.400
I should probably get going.

13:53.433 --> 13:55.202
- Sure.
- Yeah.

13:55.235 --> 13:57.004
You know, I told
the boys I'd meet 'em.

13:57.037 --> 14:00.273
Uh, don't wanna be late.
- Totally get it.

14:04.377 --> 14:08.348
Hey, thanks for listening.

14:08.381 --> 14:09.616
It means a lot.

14:10.683 --> 14:12.085
- Happy to.

14:13.520 --> 14:14.487
See 'ya.

14:21.661 --> 14:24.164
Be smart, be smart.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.900
Be smart, yeah.

14:36.076 --> 14:37.911
Don't be an idiot.

14:42.549 --> 14:44.084
- I'm an idiot.

14:44.117 --> 14:45.452
For a million reasons,
I'm an idiot.

14:45.485 --> 14:47.887
But I'd be even more
of an idiot if...

14:49.389 --> 14:50.890
- Don't be an idiot.

14:51.959 --> 14:53.193
- Things are complicated.

14:53.226 --> 14:54.527
- They don't have to be.

15:01.368 --> 15:04.437
- Things could get
pretty messy, you know.

15:09.142 --> 15:10.978
You need to relax.

15:13.046 --> 15:14.681
- I just got out of
a relationship, so...

15:16.749 --> 15:19.219
- No, not like that.

15:19.252 --> 15:21.321
But I'm just...you know.

15:21.354 --> 15:23.991
You're incredible and
I'm just not ready

15:24.024 --> 15:25.292
to be anything right now.

15:27.760 --> 15:30.197
- Look, it's just...I think...

15:31.598 --> 15:33.400
- You think too much.

16:19.112 --> 16:21.414
- * 'Cause I caught a fever

16:21.448 --> 16:23.750
* I'm heading
towards the water *

16:23.783 --> 16:27.020
* Listen to
the voice inside *

16:28.588 --> 16:34.194
* No more wasting time

16:36.263 --> 16:39.666
* Do you want to meet me
where the sunlight shines? *

