34:08.847 --> 34:10.582
- Did something happen,
Scarlett?

34:10.616 --> 34:12.451
- Nothing like that.

34:12.484 --> 34:14.086
I just found this video
of him online

34:14.120 --> 34:15.621
playing at his graduation.
His friend, Billy...

34:15.654 --> 34:17.756
- Oh...
- Dell, I'm so sorry.

34:17.789 --> 34:20.326
- Next time you wanna help,
just bring him straight here.

34:21.427 --> 34:22.828
I'm gonna go check on him.

34:22.861 --> 34:25.197
Get started on those stalls.
- Yes, ma'am.

34:30.469 --> 34:33.239
- Well, wonders never cease.

34:33.272 --> 34:35.607
- Whatever, man.
I told you, we're not a thing.

34:35.641 --> 34:37.643
- Mm-hmm.

34:37.676 --> 34:39.111
- Gah!

34:41.547 --> 34:43.382
Last night was insane.

34:43.415 --> 34:45.151
- Yeah, the crowd really
seemed to dig it.

34:45.184 --> 34:46.685
- More than dug it.

34:46.718 --> 34:48.387
How you feelin' about it all?

34:48.420 --> 34:50.889
- You know, I'm just
goin' with the flow.

34:50.922 --> 34:52.258
Seeing where it takes us.

34:54.160 --> 34:56.228
- Well, let's just say
I'm not sure which one of us

34:56.262 --> 34:57.796
is gonna regret
this girl more.

35:18.584 --> 35:21.687
- Well, this is wonderful.
Thank you so much.

35:21.720 --> 35:22.921
- Oh, chicken's
a little rubbery.

35:22.954 --> 35:24.590
But what are
you gonna do, huh?

35:24.623 --> 35:26.892
- No, it's great.
It's great, right, Jake?

35:26.925 --> 35:29.561
Jake?

35:29.595 --> 35:30.662
- Thank you.

35:30.696 --> 35:32.464
- No problem, buddy.

35:32.498 --> 35:35.567
- So I heard you guys partnered
up doing a project in class.

35:35.601 --> 35:37.369
How did that turn out?

35:40.239 --> 35:41.773
- It was fine, I guess.

35:45.211 --> 35:46.845
- A frog.

35:46.878 --> 35:50.216
I love frogs.

35:50.249 --> 35:52.751
- Yeah, we dissected it.

35:52.784 --> 35:55.454
It smelled like formaldehyde.
It was disgusting.

35:55.487 --> 35:58.457
Its legs were
like rubber and slimy.

35:58.490 --> 36:00.426
Then we cut down
its stomach and guts and...

36:00.459 --> 36:01.660
- Okay, all right.

36:03.762 --> 36:04.896
- Sorry, I brought that up.

36:06.765 --> 36:09.601
We're all here.

36:09.635 --> 36:12.304
Probably best we just
talk this thing out.

36:13.605 --> 36:15.241
Why doesn't
she have to be here?

36:15.274 --> 36:16.642
- Because this isn't
about her, sweetheart.

36:16.675 --> 36:18.344
This is about...hey!

36:18.377 --> 36:19.611
Daphne?

36:19.645 --> 36:20.879
Hey, where are you...
Daphne Conrad!

36:20.912 --> 36:22.281
Come back here right now!

36:22.314 --> 36:24.182
- Let me talk to her.
- Oh, boy.

36:25.617 --> 36:27.386
- I think I need to deal
with this, all right?

36:27.419 --> 36:29.755
- But I don't think
it's about you and Daphne.

36:29.788 --> 36:31.457
I think it's about
me and Daphne.

36:32.624 --> 36:34.326
Just let me try.

36:36.528 --> 36:37.696
- Yeah.

36:47.306 --> 36:48.607
- Go away!

36:48.640 --> 36:49.975
- You think you could
give me a minute?

36:52.844 --> 36:54.613
Then I promise I will
leave you alone.

36:58.917 --> 37:00.486
- Okay.

37:14.700 --> 37:17.569
Listen.

37:17.603 --> 37:19.438
I'm basically scared
all the time.

37:21.407 --> 37:24.576
I never really...

37:24.610 --> 37:27.379
felt like I was worth
much of anything

37:27.413 --> 37:29.548
because, honestly,
I was never cool

37:29.581 --> 37:32.818
and I wasn't
particularly smart.

37:32.851 --> 37:37.689
I wasn't talented,
so I made most of my decisions

37:37.723 --> 37:41.660
out of fear which turned out
to be a complete disaster.

37:41.693 --> 37:47.466
Which is why I am determined
not to do that anymore.

37:47.499 --> 37:49.735
But it's really, really tough

37:49.768 --> 37:51.537
because I'm still afraid.

37:55.006 --> 37:58.844
The thing is, I think that you
are such an incredible person.

37:58.877 --> 38:03.315
You are a beautiful
and talented artist

38:03.349 --> 38:05.717
and I see so much of
your mother in you.

38:08.754 --> 38:11.056
And I really wanted to get
to know you better

38:11.089 --> 38:14.860
and I guess that's probably
why I've been

38:14.893 --> 38:17.496
going about this all wrong

38:17.529 --> 38:21.567
because I'm just
scared, Daphne.

38:21.600 --> 38:25.003
I'm scared that I'm gonna
screw it all up

38:25.036 --> 38:26.838
and let everybody down.

38:26.872 --> 38:30.709
Jake and Deacon and you.

38:32.778 --> 38:34.513
- Yes, of course, you.

38:36.848 --> 38:40.652
Do you have any idea how much
that man downstairs loves you?

38:40.686 --> 38:44.456
You're his entire world

38:44.490 --> 38:47.793
and I feel like
I'm sort of messing that up

38:47.826 --> 38:49.861
for you guys, you know?

38:52.498 --> 38:53.865
- It's just really hard.

38:53.899 --> 38:55.000
- Of course, it is.

38:57.803 --> 39:00.772
Which is why you need
to hear this part.

39:00.806 --> 39:02.073
This was the part that
I was scared

39:02.107 --> 39:04.376
to tell you the whole time.

39:04.410 --> 39:05.343
But...

39:08.814 --> 39:11.883
You need to know that
I'm not trying

39:11.917 --> 39:14.119
to replace your mother, okay?

39:16.955 --> 39:20.626
I couldn't and I wouldn't.

39:22.828 --> 39:25.531
And I'm not trying to take
your father from you either.

39:27.766 --> 39:30.135
He has such a big heart,

39:30.168 --> 39:33.672
probably bigger than
any man I've ever met.

39:33.705 --> 39:37.075
And he has enough room
for you and Maddie

39:37.108 --> 39:39.778
and me and your mother.

39:42.814 --> 39:44.049
Forever, your mother.

39:44.082 --> 39:47.118
Which is a little daunting.

39:47.152 --> 39:50.422
But I'm trying to handle it.

39:52.057 --> 39:55.527
The thing is, what I want...

39:55.561 --> 39:58.497
and I really,
really want it...

39:58.530 --> 40:04.670
is just to be your friend...

40:07.573 --> 40:09.808
if such a thing is possible.

40:11.242 --> 40:12.811
- I'm sorry.

40:20.886 --> 40:22.488
I'm the troublemaker here.

40:32.531 --> 40:35.200
- Why is it every time I try
to do something good or right,

40:35.233 --> 40:37.769
it blows up in my face?

40:37.803 --> 40:39.705
- Happens to the best of us.

40:39.738 --> 40:41.840
- Dell, I did not mean
to make things worse.

40:41.873 --> 40:42.974
I truly didn't.

40:44.242 --> 40:45.477
- Walk with me.

40:49.180 --> 40:51.950
There's a verse by Leonard Cohen
that I've always loved.

40:51.983 --> 40:53.785
You know, one
where he talks about

40:53.819 --> 40:55.821
ringing the bells
that still can ring?

40:55.854 --> 40:57.155
- Yeah.

40:57.188 --> 40:59.758
- Well, the point is,
no one is perfect.

40:59.791 --> 41:01.560
Everyone is cracked.

41:01.593 --> 41:04.796
But it's the cracks that let
our light shine through.

41:04.830 --> 41:06.565
- So beautiful.

41:13.071 --> 41:17.543
- * Wasting time

41:23.081 --> 41:25.517
* 'Cause I caught a fever

41:25.551 --> 41:28.920
* I'm headin'
towards the water *

41:28.954 --> 41:33.659
* Listen to the
voice inside *

41:35.627 --> 41:39.064
* No more

41:39.097 --> 41:43.168
* Wasting time
